{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17646310","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17646310"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T20:28:39+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T20:28:39+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18171"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18171","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18171"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.59,0.09,0.05,0.23,0.05]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10885"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"79290"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10885","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10885"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18171"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"64612"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4931"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"7302"},{"type":"tags","id":"7312"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"25315"},{"type":"contributions","id":"25318"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"79290","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/79290"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following features is characteristic of the lumbar vertebrae?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Spinous processes are short, hatchet-shaped","Circular vertebral foramen","Presence of transverse foramina","Bifid spinous processes","Costal facets on the transverse processes"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe lumbar vertebrae are characterised by their large, kidney-shaped bodies and \u003Cstrong\u003Eshort, hatchet-shaped spinous processes\u003C/strong\u003E. These features provide stability and support for the lower back, which bears much of the body\u0027s weight.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Ecircular vertebral foramen\u003C/strong\u003E is a feature of thoracic vertebrae, not lumbar vertebrae. The lumbar vertebral foramen are triangular.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETransverse foramina\u003C/strong\u003E are found in cervical vertebrae, not lumbar vertebrae. These foramina allow passage of the vertebral arteries.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBifid spinous processes\u003C/strong\u003E are characteristic of cervical vertebrae. This feature allows for greater flexibility in the neck region.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECostal facets\u003C/strong\u003E on the transverse processes are found in thoracic vertebrae, where they articulate with the ribs.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The lumbar vertebrae are characterised by large, kidney-shaped bodies and short, hatchet-shaped spinous processes.","The vertebral foramen in lumbar vertebrae is triangular, not circular.","Understanding the anatomical differences between vertebrae in different regions of the spine is crucial for diagnosis and treatment of spinal conditions."],"references":["West, S. G. (2019). Anatomy and physiology of the musculoskeletal system. Rheumatology Secrets E-Book: Rheumatology Secrets E-Book, 17","Henson B, Kadiyala B, Edens MA. Anatomy, Back, Muscles. [Updated 2023 Aug 14]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK537074/","Hutson, M., \u0026 Ward, A. (Eds.). (2015). Oxford textbook of musculoskeletal medicine. Oxford University Press","Rockwood, C. A., Wirth, M. A., \u0026 Fehringer, E. V. (2016). Rockwood and Matsen\u0027s The Shoulder E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","DeSai C, Reddy V, Agarwal A. Anatomy, Back, Vertebral Column. [Updated 2023 Aug 8]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK525969/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"64612"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18171"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"64612","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/64612"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-13T22:47:05+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-13T22:47:24+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10885"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"79290"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"4931","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/4931"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\